---
// TEMPORARY preview page for picking new homepage sections.
// Renders 5 variants each of two proposed sections (placed after the hero):
//   Section 1 - Why documentation matters + the broken current state (84% stat).
//   Section 2 - Use cases, the two largest: public docs + internal wikis.
// Pick one of each (e.g. "1C + 2A") and the winners get wired into index.astro;
// this page is then deleted. Stats are attributed per the fact bank.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Tabs from '../components/Tabs.astro';
---

<Base title="docstube - section variants (preview)" description="Internal preview of candidate homepage sections.">
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-line bg-paper">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-14 text-center sm:px-8">
        <span class="chip"><span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-400"></span> internal preview, not linked</span>
        <h1 class="mt-5 text-balance text-3xl font-extrabold sm:text-4xl">Pick a direction for three new sections.</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[16px] leading-relaxed text-muted">
          Several variants each, meant to sit after the hero. Each is labelled (1A ... 3E) in the dark bar above it.
          Tell me which one of each you want - say something like "1G, 2A and 3B" - and I'll wire them into the
          homepage and delete this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- SECTION 1 - Why docs matter + the broken state               -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <div class="bg-ink">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center gap-3 px-5 py-3 sm:px-8">
        <span class="font-display text-[15px] font-bold text-paper">Section 1</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-[12px] text-paper/60">Why documentation matters, and why the current state is broken</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ===== ROUND 5 (way more content per tile) ===== -->
    <div class="bg-brand-900">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-3.5 sm:px-8">
        <p class="font-display text-[14px] font-bold text-paper">Round 5 - way more content per tile</p>
        <p class="font-mono text-[11.5px] text-paper/80">1S-1U: each tile now has a lead, an example, a "how it shows up" list, and a consequence. Same content, three looks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ---------- 1S: content-dense, vivid light ---------- -->
    <div class="border-y border-line bg-ink/95"><div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-2 sm:px-8"><span class="rounded bg-brand-500 px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-[12px] font-bold text-paper">1S</span> <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-[12px] text-paper/70">content-dense, vivid light</span></div></div>
    <section class="border-b border-line bg-canvas">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-20 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-5 text-center">
          <span class="eyebrow">Why this matters</span>
          <h2 class="max-w-2xl text-balance text-3xl font-bold sm:text-[42px] sm:leading-[1.06]">Everyone needs the docs. Every way we make them is broken.</h2>
          <p class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-2 text-[15px] text-muted"><span class="font-display text-[26px] font-extrabold leading-none gradient-text">84%</span> call technical docs their number-one way to learn. <a href="https://survey.stackoverflow.co/2024/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="font-mono text-[11px] text-muted underline decoration-line-strong underline-offset-2 hover:text-brand-600">source</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-14 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-danger/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#fdf0ef] via-paper to-paper p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-danger/12 text-danger"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9" /><path d="M12 8v4.5l3 1.8" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold text-ink">It goes stale</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full border border-danger/20 bg-danger/8 px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-danger">every release</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-relaxed text-muted">Code ships every day; hand-written docs don't move. Examples rot and signatures drift until the page is full of statements that used to be true.</p>
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-line bg-paper font-mono text-[12.5px]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-danger/8 px-3.5 py-2 text-danger"><span class="font-bold">-</span> getSession()<span class="ml-auto text-[10px] opacity-70">docs</span></div><div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-t border-line px-3.5 py-2 text-ink-soft"><span class="font-bold text-pass">+</span> getSession(opts)<span class="ml-auto text-[10px] text-muted">code</span></div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-danger">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-danger">&bull;</span> A sample that throws the moment you paste it</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-danger">&bull;</span> An option renamed three sprints ago</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-danger">&bull;</span> A "returns a Session" that now returns a Client</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-line pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><span class="font-semibold text-ink">The reader</span> copies code that no longer runs, and assumes they did it wrong.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-flag/25 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#fdf6ea] via-paper to-paper p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-flag/15 text-flag"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 12s3.6-6.5 10-6.5S22 12 22 12" /><path d="M2 12s3.6 6.5 10 6.5S22 12 22 12" /><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2.5" /><path d="M4 20 20 4" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold text-ink">It assumes too much</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full border border-flag/25 bg-flag/8 px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-flag">most pages</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-relaxed text-muted">Whoever wrote the code can't un-know it. The obvious step gets skipped, internal names leak in, and the context a newcomer needs never gets written down.</p>
            <div class="space-y-2"><div class="rounded-xl border border-line bg-paper px-3.5 py-2.5 font-mono text-[12.5px] text-ink-soft">init with your <span class="rounded bg-flag/15 px-1 text-flag">workspace token</span></div><div class="ml-10 w-fit rounded-xl rounded-tl-none border border-flag/25 bg-flag/8 px-3 py-1.5 text-[12px] text-flag">where do I get one of those?</div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-flag">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-flag">&bull;</span> A term defined nowhere, used everywhere</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-flag">&bull;</span> A prerequisite nobody mentioned</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-flag">&bull;</span> Jargon that only makes sense from the inside</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-line pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><span class="font-semibold text-ink">The reader</span> stalls on step one, and never reaches step two.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-brand-200 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-paper to-paper p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-brand-100 text-brand-600"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 3v5h5" /><path d="M7 3h7l5 5v10a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2z" /><path d="M8.5 17 15 10.5" /><path d="M15 17 8.5 10.5" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold text-ink">It never gets written</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full border border-brand-200 bg-brand-50 px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-brand-700">the hard parts</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-relaxed text-muted">Docs are the chore that loses to every deadline. Configuration, edge cases, the gnarly migration - the pages readers need most are the ones that stay empty.</p>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-dashed border-line-strong bg-paper px-4 py-3.5 font-mono text-[12.5px]"><div class="text-ink-soft">## Configuration</div><div class="mt-1 text-muted">// TODO: write this</div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-700">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-500">&bull;</span> A "coming soon" that shipped two years ago</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-500">&bull;</span> A heading with one sentence under it</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-500">&bull;</span> The exact error you hit, documented nowhere</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-line pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><span class="font-semibold text-ink">The reader</span> goes looking for the hard part, and finds a stub.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-[#ddd5fb] bg-gradient-to-br from-[#f4f0fe] via-paper to-paper p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl text-[#6d4ee6]" style="background:#e9e3fd"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3l1.7 4.6L18 9l-4.3 1.4L12 15l-1.7-4.6L6 9l4.3-1.4L12 3z" /><path d="M18.5 13.5l.7 1.9 1.9.7-1.9.7-.7 1.9-.7-1.9-1.9-.7 1.9-.7.7-1.9z" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold text-ink">And AI doesn't fix it</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-[#6d4ee6]" style="background:#ece6fd">30+ / page</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-relaxed text-muted">Point a model at your repo and the pages read beautifully. Check them against the source and the problems pour out - fluent, confident, and wrong.</p>
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-line bg-paper"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3.5 py-2 font-mono text-[11px]"><span class="text-ink-soft">review · auth.mdx</span><span class="ml-auto font-semibold text-[#6d4ee6]">30+ issues</span></div><div class="h-1.5 w-full bg-line"><div class="h-full" style="width:80%;background:#7c5cf0"></div></div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#6d4ee6]">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color:#6d4ee6">&bull;</span> Methods and flags that don't exist</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color:#6d4ee6">&bull;</span> Two samples on one page that contradict</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color:#6d4ee6">&bull;</span> Claims with nothing in the code behind them</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-line pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-ink-soft"><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Worse than stale</span> - it's wrong in ways that look right.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ---------- 1T: content-dense, dark ---------- -->
    <div class="border-y border-line bg-ink/95"><div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-2 sm:px-8"><span class="rounded bg-brand-500 px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-[12px] font-bold text-paper">1T</span> <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-[12px] text-paper/70">content-dense, dark</span></div></div>
    <section class="border-b border-line bg-night">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-20 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-5 text-center">
          <span class="font-mono text-[12px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-brand-300">Why this matters</span>
          <h2 class="max-w-2xl text-balance font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#eafaf6] sm:text-[42px] sm:leading-[1.06]">The docs are broken. AI didn't save them.</h2>
          <p class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-2 text-[15px] text-[#9fc4be]"><span class="font-display text-[26px] font-extrabold leading-none" style="background:linear-gradient(92deg,#5fd6c4,#9fe6d8);-webkit-background-clip:text;background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">84%</span> call technical docs their number-one way to learn. <a href="https://survey.stackoverflow.co/2024/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="font-mono text-[11px] text-[#7fa6a0] underline decoration-[#2a4a46] underline-offset-2 hover:text-brand-300">source</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-14 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-[#1f3634] bg-[#102322] p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-[#f0716b]" style="background:rgba(240,113,107,0.13)"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9" /><path d="M12 8v4.5l3 1.8" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[19px] font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">It goes stale</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-[#f0716b]" style="background:rgba(240,113,107,0.1)">every release</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-[#9fc4be]">Code ships every day; hand-written docs don't move. Examples rot and signatures drift until the page is full of statements that used to be true.</p>
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[#1f3634] font-mono text-[12.5px]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3.5 py-2 text-[#f0716b]" style="background:rgba(240,113,107,0.08)"><span class="font-bold">-</span> getSession()</div><div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-t border-[#1f3634] px-3.5 py-2 text-[#bfe0db]"><span class="font-bold text-[#54c98b]">+</span> getSession(opts)</div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#f0716b]">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-[#bfe0db]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f0716b]">&bull;</span> A sample that throws the moment you paste it</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f0716b]">&bull;</span> An option renamed three sprints ago</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f0716b]">&bull;</span> A "returns a Session" that now returns a Client</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-[#1f3634] pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-[#9fc4be]"><span class="font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">The reader</span> copies code that no longer runs, and blames themselves.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-[#1f3634] bg-[#102322] p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-[#f3c64a]" style="background:rgba(243,198,74,0.13)"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 12s3.6-6.5 10-6.5S22 12 22 12" /><path d="M2 12s3.6 6.5 10 6.5S22 12 22 12" /><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2.5" /><path d="M4 20 20 4" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[19px] font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">It assumes too much</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-[#f3c64a]" style="background:rgba(243,198,74,0.1)">most pages</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-[#9fc4be]">Whoever wrote the code can't un-know it. The obvious step gets skipped, internal names leak in, and the context a newcomer needs never gets written down.</p>
            <div class="space-y-2"><div class="rounded-xl border border-[#1f3634] px-3.5 py-2.5 font-mono text-[12.5px] text-[#bfe0db]">init with your <span class="rounded px-1 text-[#f3c64a]" style="background:rgba(243,198,74,0.16)">workspace token</span></div><div class="ml-10 w-fit rounded-xl rounded-tl-none px-3 py-1.5 text-[12px] text-[#f3c64a]" style="background:rgba(243,198,74,0.1)">where do I get one?</div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#f3c64a]">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-[#bfe0db]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f3c64a]">&bull;</span> A term defined nowhere, used everywhere</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f3c64a]">&bull;</span> A prerequisite nobody mentioned</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#f3c64a]">&bull;</span> Jargon that only makes sense from the inside</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-[#1f3634] pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-[#9fc4be]"><span class="font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">The reader</span> stalls on step one, and never reaches step two.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border border-[#1f3634] bg-[#102322] p-7 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-brand-300" style="background:rgba(54,177,176,0.14)"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 3v5h5" /><path d="M7 3h7l5 5v10a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2z" /><path d="M8.5 17 15 10.5" /><path d="M15 17 8.5 10.5" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[19px] font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">It never gets written</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-brand-300" style="background:rgba(54,177,176,0.12)">the hard parts</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-[#9fc4be]">Docs are the chore that loses to every deadline. Configuration, edge cases, the gnarly migration - the pages readers need most are the ones that stay empty.</p>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-dashed border-[#2a4a46] px-4 py-3.5 font-mono text-[12.5px]"><div class="text-[#bfe0db]">## Configuration</div><div class="mt-1 text-[#6f8e8a]">// TODO: write this</div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-300">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-[#bfe0db]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-300">&bull;</span> A "coming soon" that shipped two years ago</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-300">&bull;</span> A heading with one sentence under it</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-300">&bull;</span> The exact error you hit, documented nowhere</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-[#1f3634] pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-[#9fc4be]"><span class="font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">The reader</span> goes looking for the hard part, and finds a stub.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl border p-7 sm:p-8" style="border-color:#352d5e;background:linear-gradient(160deg,#161430,#102322)">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-[#b3a6ff]" style="background:rgba(124,92,240,0.18)"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3l1.7 4.6L18 9l-4.3 1.4L12 15l-1.7-4.6L6 9l4.3-1.4L12 3z" /><path d="M18.5 13.5l.7 1.9 1.9.7-1.9.7-.7 1.9-.7-1.9-1.9-.7 1.9-.7.7-1.9z" /></svg></span><h3 class="font-display text-[19px] font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">And AI doesn't fix it</h3><span class="ml-auto rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold text-[#b3a6ff]" style="background:rgba(124,92,240,0.2)">30+ / page</span></div>
            <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-[#9fc4be]">Point a model at your repo and the pages read beautifully. Check them against the source and the problems pour out - fluent, confident, and wrong.</p>
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[#352d5e]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3.5 py-2 font-mono text-[11px] text-[#bfe0db]">review · auth.mdx<span class="ml-auto font-semibold text-[#b3a6ff]">30+ issues</span></div><div class="h-1.5 w-full" style="background:#241f45"><div class="h-full" style="width:80%;background:#7c5cf0"></div></div></div>
            <div><p class="font-mono text-[10.5px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#b3a6ff]">How it shows up</p><ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-[13px] text-[#bfe0db]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#b3a6ff]">&bull;</span> Methods and flags that don't exist</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#b3a6ff]">&bull;</span> Two samples on one page that contradict</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#b3a6ff]">&bull;</span> Claims with nothing in the code behind them</li></ul></div>
            <p class="mt-auto border-t border-[#352d5e] pt-3.5 text-[13px] text-[#9fc4be]"><span class="font-semibold text-[#eafaf6]">Worse than stale</span> - it's wrong in ways that look right.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ---------- 1U: content-dense, clean editorial ---------- -->
    <div class="border-y border-line bg-ink/95"><div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-2 sm:px-8"><span class="rounded bg-brand-500 px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-[12px] font-bold text-paper">1U</span> <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-[12px] text-paper/70">content-dense, clean editorial (numbered)</span></div></div>
